It was not far removed from Cirrha, butI doubt the con· nexion between the names which Prof. Palmer assumes (on Sat. 11. 3, 82). Many persons came to reside there for medical treat- ment [ib. 166). There was another Anticyra on the Spercheius at the head ol the Maliac Gall, and it is asserted (but only on the late authority of Stephanus) that hellebore grew there too, and that the natives professed to have eured Heracles ol his madness.
